    <updated>2019-04-13T17:10:58.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p class="description">This post is for adjusting my blog theme and presenting some fantastic features of NexT.</p><p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/zjysteven/blog/images/img/2019/0412-Toy-Post-1.png" alt="note example" style="width:100%"></p><a id="more"></a><hr><h2 id="Code-Block"><a href="#Code-Block" class="headerlink" title="Code Block"></a>Code Block</h2><p><span class="inline-toc">1.</span> Let’s try some code!</p><figure class="highlight python"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> numpy <span class="keyword">as</span> np</span><br><span class="line"><span class="keyword">import</span> matplotlib.pyplot <span class="keyword">as</span> plt</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h2 id="Note"><a href="#Note" class="headerlink" title="Note"></a>Note</h2><p><span class="inline-toc">2.</span> Let’s try some note blocks!</p><div class="note "><p>This is default note without any style. </p></div><div class="note default"><p>This is “default” note. </p></div><div class="note primary"><p>This is “primary” note. </p></div><div class="note info"><p>This is “info” note. </p></div><div class="note success"><p>This is “success” note. </p></div><div class="note warning"><p>This is “warning” note. </p></div><div class="note danger"><p>This is “danger” note. </p></div><div class="note danger no-icon"><p>This is “danger” note without icon. Just use <code>note xxxx no-icon</code> to trigger this style.</p></div><p>These note blocks are actually built-in features for the latest <a href="https://theme-next.org/docs/tag-plugins/note#No-icon-note" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NexT v7</a>. However, as I uses NexT v5.1.4 as the basic theme, I manually added correponding codes to my <code>custom.styl</code>.</p>]]></content>
    
